Lizeka Tandwa, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories We speak to Valarie Mhere, the sister of late Top Billing presenter Simba Mhere. Watch her tell us about her family's grieving process and the answers they are still waiting for from police and the National Prosecuting Authority.WATCHJohannesburg - The man accused of killing&nbsp;Top Billing presenter Simba Mhere and his friend Kady-Shay O'Bryan in a car crash appeared briefly at the Randburg Magistrate's Court on Wednesday.&nbsp;Preshalin Naidoo faces two counts of culpable homicide and additional charges of reckless or negligent driving and inconsiderate driving.&nbsp;He appeared in court dressed in a fitted grey designer suit, accompanied a group of people presumed to be his family and friends.&nbsp;The court heard that experts who were due to testify on Wednesday would only arrive in Johannesburg on Thursday.&nbsp;The matter was postponed to February 9. On Tuesday, the court rejected Naidoo's lawyer's application to dismiss the charges.Naidoo's VW Polo GTI crashed into Mhere's car on William Nicol Drive, Fourways, in the early hours of January 31, 2015. Mhere's father Joseph was also a passenger in the car. He survived.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.